# AQNAS port registry — TEMPLATE
#
# This file is a template. Your real allocations live in `ports.conf` (which is
# gitignored). On first run of setup.sh or allocate-port.sh, this template is
# copied to `ports.conf` if one doesn't exist yet.
#
# Why split: the studio repo is public; specific port allocations are operational
# state that doesn't need to be public.
#
# Format: {project} = {port}
# Range: 8000–8099 (see the port-registry skill)
#
# Sub-ranges:
#   8000–8009 — studio infrastructure (reserved for future)
#   8010–8089 — normal projects (allocate here)
#   8090–8099 — temporary/scratch projects
#
# To reserve a port, run:
#   $AQNAS_STUDIO_ROOT/claude-config/skills/port-registry/scripts/allocate-port.sh {project}
# (allocate-port.sh appends atomically with flock)

# Studio infrastructure (8000–8009)
# (none yet)

# Projects (8010–8089)
# e.g.
# my-first-app = 8010
# my-second-app = 8011

# Scratch (8090–8099)
# (none)
